    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "That makes sense. I've noticed some analysts in the field argue that these demographic shifts usually signify a move toward more diverse, lower-income populations, which they see as a primary indicator of decreasing neighborhood safety and property value stability. Do you think that's a valid way to model the risk, or is that just an oversimplification of the data?",
